2022 was daunting, giving, and slow moving. Probably the most energetically slow year I’ve had. 2022 was a year I recouped from having experienced so much the year prior. The grief of losing two childhood fur babies and the stress of a business opening under hostile circumstances was enough to send me into a year of introspect, a LOT of it. I discovered what I genuinely give a sh!t about, what is deserving of time and energy, cutting out the dead weight, how to let love & light back in after shunning everything around you, and building back up new bridges I thought were set to combust. It was a weird rollercoaster this year. So many unexpected twists and turns. I try to tell myself hardships are given to make room for the calm and peace you need most, so honestly I can just get through those moments. But above it all, walking through hell in 2021 opened a path to meeting my love, moving in together and gaining two more sweet kitties. It granted me new friendships & new alignments with ones I’ve had in the past. It quite honestly turned the table on me, and I’m thankful for that. As I continue to let this “smoke” billow and rest, I feel a pull to gain momentum again soon. The toughest things we deem as so scary can be the biggest blessings in disguise once we look back on our timelines. Stay grateful 🤍

I see some new followers here so allow me to reintroduce myself! My names Rachel but you can call me Rach, Behm girl, pet portrait girl or my closest friends call me laser ⚡️ I’m 28 and have been tattooing for about 8 years now (I think?) I love cats and Taylor swift, sweets and all things 4-2-0 🤗 outside of work I like to dabble in photography and designing various things. I’m from a small town of about 7,000 people and have been out of that place since 2017. I’m a Philly gal food fanatic and my friends and family are my world! OH! I’m obsessed with Dom Dolla too. If you can’t tell, I’m quite the juxtaposition. You can book with me either through my website or via email, rachelbehmbookings@gmail.com!
